"{\"uid\": \"cityam.com-olympic-champions-to-receive-prize-money-for-first-time-at-paris-2024-games\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 45, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 47, \"to\": 92, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 94, \"to\": 139, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By:Frank Dalleres  Sports Editor  Olympic champions will receive prize money for the first time this year after World Athletics announced gold medallists at the Paris 2024 Games would be paid $50,000 (\\u00a339,400) each.\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 356, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 253, \"end\": 268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999995600319, \"rank\": 4.3999758196107613e-10, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletics is the first sport to financially reward its stars for success at the Olympics, which has stayed true to its amateur ethos by never offering prize money.\", \"from\": 358, \"to\": 521, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Winners of all 48 athletics events will receive a payout from the world governing body, which says it will extend the benefit to silver and bronze medallists from the LA 2028 Olympics.\", \"from\": 523, \"to\": 707, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 693, \"end\": 706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"2028 Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The introduction of prize money for Olympic gold medallists is a pivotal moment for World Athletics and the sport of athletics as a whole, underscoring our commitment to empowering the athletes and recognising the critical role they play in the success of any Olympic Games,\\\" said World Athletics president Lord Coe.\", \"from\": 709, \"to\": 1026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 794, \"end\": 809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999995600319, \"rank\": 4.3999758196107613e-10, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 991, \"end\": 1006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999995600319, \"rank\": 4.3999758196107613e-10, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 1017, \"end\": 1025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lord Coe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"While it is impossible to put a marketable value on winning an Olympic medal, or on the commitment and focus it takes to even represent your country at an Olympic Games, I think it is important we start somewhere and make sure some of the revenues generated by our athletes at the Olympic Games are directly returned to those who make the Games the global spectacle that it is.\\\"\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1407, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stay in the game with The Turnover: your weekly roundup of sport business news, expert analysis and behind\\u2011the\\u2011scenes stories from City\\u202fAM's sports desk.\", \"from\": 1409, \"to\": 1562, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The size of the payouts is modest compared to those on offer elsewhere in sport - the average salary of a Premier League footballer is around \\u00a33m, for instance.\", \"from\": 1564, \"to\": 1724, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1670, \"end\": 1684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Premier_League\", \"score\": 0.9999540517064408, \"rank\": 4.577556885349638e-05, \"text\": \"Premier League\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Premier_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Premier_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Butthe moveis nonetheless a milestone for the Olympics, and recognition that it will be increasingly difficult to justify asking the stars of its core events to compete for glory alone.\", \"from\": 1726, \"to\": 1911, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Many Olympic hopefulsrely on funding grants and personal sponsorship dealsto train full-time, while others have to retain careers in order to make ends meet.\", \"from\": 1913, \"to\": 2070, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile,athletes are being offered million-dollar incentives to defect to the doping-friendly Enhanced Games, a projectCoe has derided as \\\"bollocks\\\".\", \"from\": 2072, \"to\": 2223, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While winners of individual athletics events at Paris 2024 will receive $50,000, that sum will be divided up among team members for winners of the relay races.\", \"from\": 2225, \"to\": 2384, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"World Athletics introduces prize money for Olympic gold medallists at Paris 2024, and all medallists from LA28.\", \"from\": 2386, \"to\": 2497, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2386, \"end\": 2401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999995600319, \"rank\": 4.3999758196107613e-10, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is the continuation of a journey we started back in 2015, which sees all the money World Athletics receives from the International Olympic Committee for the Olympic Games go directly back into our sport,\\\" Coe added.\", \"from\": 2499, \"to\": 2720, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2588, \"end\": 2603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999995600319, \"rank\": 4.3999758196107613e-10, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 2622, \"end\": 2653, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We started with the Olympic dividend payments to our Member Federations, which saw us distribute an extra $5m a year on top of existing grants aimed at athletics growth projects, and we are now in a position to also fund gold medal performances for athletes in Paris, with a commitment to reward all three medallists at the LA28 Olympic Games.\\\"\", \"from\": 2722, \"to\": 3067, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2984, \"end\": 2989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999996729457, \"rank\": 3.2704343920217785e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Share this article  Subscribe to the City AM newsletter to have our top stories delivered directly to your inbox.\", \"from\": 3069, \"to\": 3182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow us for breaking news and latest updates\", \"from\": 3184, \"to\": 3230, \"entities\": []}]}"